quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  26,123,"The people of 'Ad, too, disbelieved their Messengers"
  26,124,"Remember when their brother Hud asked them: \"Have you no fear of Allah"
  26,125,Rest assured that I am a trustworthy Messenger of Allah towards you
  26,126,So fear Allah and obey me
  26,127,"I do not ask you any reward for my services, for my reward will be given by the Lord of the Worlds"
  26,128,Are you erecting a monument on every high place for fun
  26,129,Are you building strong fortresses as if you are going to live here forever
  26,130,"Whenever you lay your hands on anyone, you act like cruel tyrants"
  26,131,Have fear of Allah and obey me
  26,132,Fear the One Who has given you all the things that you know
  26,133,He has given you flocks and children
  26,134,gardens and fountains
  26,135,Truly I fear for you the torment of a dreadful Day
  26,136,"They replied: \"It is the same to us whether you preach us or you are not one of the preachers"
  26,137,Such preaching is nothing but an ancient myth
  26,138,We are not going to be punished
  26,139,"So they disbelieved him and We utterly destroyed them. Surely in this story there is a great lesson, but most of these people do not learn a lesson and become believers"
  26,140,The fact is that your Lord is the Mighty as well as the Merciful